1
00:00:01,644 --> 00:00:03,761
If that letter from
President Grant was forged,

2
00:00:03,795 --> 00:00:05,062
there will be joint
congressional hearings

3
00:00:05,113 --> 00:00:07,181
- and letters of impeachment.
- Good-bye, Edison.

4
00:00:08,316 --> 00:00:09,733
<i>Previously on "Scandal"...</i>

5
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:11,267
Which one of you
forged his signature?

6
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:13,870
- I did.
- It's a federal crime. It's treason.

7
00:00:13,904 --> 00:00:16,523
I have a sworn affidavit
saying that your husband

8
00:00:16,557 --> 00:00:19,342
has failed to so much
as open his eyes.

9
00:00:19,377 --> 00:00:20,560
(Cell phone rings)
Hello?

10
00:00:20,594 --> 00:00:21,911
Hi.

11
00:00:21,963 --> 00:00:23,530
(Voice breaks) Hi.

12
00:00:25,232 --> 00:00:28,134
(Projector and camera
shutter clicking)

13
00:00:32,105 --> 00:00:33,072
Oh, hi.

14
00:00:33,107 --> 00:00:34,206
"Oh. Hi"?
(Keys jangle)

15
00:00:34,224 --> 00:00:35,441
Hello, Edison.

16
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:39,211
Olivia.

17
00:00:39,229 --> 00:00:41,798
- What?
- What's going on? With us.

18
00:00:41,832 --> 00:00:43,682
(Files rustling)
Nothing.

19
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:46,484
- Nothing's going on with us?
- Edison.

20
00:00:46,702 --> 00:00:49,104
This serious boyfriend
that you had,

21
00:00:49,138 --> 00:00:50,254
the one that you broke up with...

22
00:00:50,273 --> 00:00:51,490
Look, I have a lot to do
tomorrow,

23
00:00:51,524 --> 00:00:53,642
and I haven't had much sleep
and I'm not in the mood to...

24
00:00:53,676 --> 00:00:55,410
This serious boyfriend...
Was it Fitzgerald Grant?

25
00:00:57,763 --> 00:01:00,181
(Chuckles)

26
00:01:00,232 --> 00:01:02,150
You're asking me
if I was in a relationship

27
00:01:02,201 --> 00:01:03,668
- with the President?
- Yes.

28
00:01:03,703 --> 00:01:04,803
- He's married.
- Yes.

29
00:01:04,837 --> 00:01:05,904
- He's the President.
- Yes.

30
00:01:05,938 --> 00:01:07,655
Is this a joke?
Are you kidding?

31
00:01:07,690 --> 00:01:09,074
I'm waiting for you
to answer the question.

32
00:01:11,543 --> 00:01:13,627
You're mad because
I wouldn't let you

33
00:01:13,662 --> 00:01:14,912
into the President's
hospital room?

34
00:01:14,946 --> 00:01:19,033
Not mad. Concerned.
Wary. Suspicious.

35
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:21,369
- Don't be. - Because the
President's not your boyfriend?

36
00:01:21,403 --> 00:01:24,438
You really want to stop
asking me that.

37
00:01:24,689 --> 00:01:26,356
I've been racking my brain
trying to find a reason

38
00:01:26,374 --> 00:01:28,259
why you'd be stupid enough
to willingly attempt

39
00:01:28,293 --> 00:01:29,727
to defraud the American people,

40
00:01:29,761 --> 00:01:31,295
and the only reason
I can come up with

41
00:01:31,329 --> 00:01:32,563
for why you'd be in so deep

42
00:01:32,597 --> 00:01:35,031
is because you were his mistress.

43
00:01:35,066 --> 00:01:39,002
Five...
that's sexist and insulting.

44
00:01:39,036 --> 00:01:40,954
You'd never suggest
Scooter Libby

45
00:01:40,988 --> 00:01:42,539
was screwing Dick Cheney.

46
00:01:42,573 --> 00:01:45,225
Four... the lengths you're going
to try to twist this

47
00:01:45,276 --> 00:01:47,210
into a conspiracy are
cause for concern.

48
00:01:47,245 --> 00:01:48,745
You should speak to
someone about that.

49
00:01:48,763 --> 00:01:51,214
Three... the President
is awake and talking,

50
00:01:51,249 --> 00:01:54,201
and the suggestion that he isn't
is partisan political crap

51
00:01:54,235 --> 00:01:57,053
that I thought you had
enough integrity to rise above.

52
00:01:57,087 --> 00:01:58,838
Two...
in the past three minutes,

53
00:01:58,872 --> 00:02:00,740
you've called me a criminal,
a whore,

54
00:02:00,774 --> 00:02:02,442
an idiot, and a liar,

55
00:02:02,476 --> 00:02:04,744
so this is pretty much the
last time we'll be speaking,

56
00:02:04,795 --> 00:02:07,730
so one...who I am or
am <i>not</i> screwing,

57
00:02:07,765 --> 00:02:09,131
what am or am not doing,

58
00:02:09,149 --> 00:02:12,251
is no longer any of
your damn business.

59
00:02:12,286 --> 00:02:14,420
You forget how well
I know you.

60
00:02:14,455 --> 00:02:17,623
You this angry?
You have something to hide.

61
00:02:17,658 --> 00:02:19,142
I have been summoned
to a meeting

62
00:02:19,176 --> 00:02:21,210
at the white house tomorrow
with acting President Langston

63
00:02:21,245 --> 00:02:22,645
about the letter
of reinstatement,

64
00:02:22,679 --> 00:02:24,981
which she says is a forgery.
(Scoffs)

65
00:02:25,015 --> 00:02:26,866
And she's going to tell that
to the entire cabinet

66
00:02:26,917 --> 00:02:28,684
first thing in the morning.

67
00:02:28,718 --> 00:02:31,220
So if there's something
that you want to tell me,

68
00:02:31,255 --> 00:02:34,856
do it now, when I still
have time to help you.

69
00:02:51,307 --> 00:02:52,691
(Beep)

70
00:02:52,742 --> 00:02:55,677
Cyrus, we have a problem.

71
00:02:56,111 --> 00:02:58,547
(Projector
and camera shutter clicking)

72
00:02:58,665 --> 00:03:01,683
sync and corrections by bellows
www.addic7ed.com

73
00:03:02,218 --> 00:03:04,352
Increasing our military
presence in Asia

74
00:03:04,386 --> 00:03:05,770
costs money, Governor.

75
00:03:05,804 --> 00:03:08,189
Which is why we'd have to
shift our defense spend...

76
00:03:08,223 --> 00:03:10,091
Can't just run to daddy
and ask for the dough

77
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:11,792
on this one.
(Laughter)

78
00:03:11,810 --> 00:03:13,127
(Lowered voice) Use the attack line.
Attack line.

79
00:03:13,145 --> 00:03:15,430
Go to my web site.
Look at my spending plans.

80
00:03:15,464 --> 00:03:17,131
- Do the math.
- Oh, no.

81
00:03:17,149 --> 00:03:18,683
Now he's giving
the voters homework.

82
00:03:18,734 --> 00:03:20,518
Fiscal budget, we can afford to
make this common reallocation.

83
00:03:20,569 --> 00:03:21,769
I'm sorry, Governor.
We have to move on.

84
00:03:21,787 --> 00:03:23,004
I deserve a chance
to respond.

85
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:25,072
You think you deserve
everything, don't you, Governor?

86
00:03:25,107 --> 00:03:26,524
(Laughter)
No... (Chuckles)

87
00:03:26,575 --> 00:03:28,276
No. If we could get
back to medicare.

88
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:29,610
Look. Look.
Governor Reston...

89
00:03:29,644 --> 00:03:31,145
- I can't.
- Tell me when it's over.

90
00:03:31,163 --> 00:03:33,664
You need 270 electoral
college votes to win, right?

91
00:03:33,699 --> 00:03:36,451
And you've got 188 locked up
from the deep red states.

92
00:03:36,485 --> 00:03:38,002
So you need a pickup
of 82 votes,

93
00:03:38,036 --> 00:03:40,288
most likely from a
combination of Ohio,

94
00:03:40,322 --> 00:03:43,040
Florida, Virginia, Colorado,
Nevada, North Carolina.

95
00:03:43,091 --> 00:03:46,127
So, basically, you can't afford
to lose more than one of them.

96
00:03:46,161 --> 00:03:47,995
- And if I do?
- You're toast.

97
00:03:48,013 --> 00:03:49,647
Did the debate
move the needle at all?

98
00:03:49,681 --> 00:03:52,166
Not in your favor.
I'm sorry, Governor.

99
00:03:52,184 --> 00:03:54,101
Numbers don't lie.

100
00:03:55,271 --> 00:03:56,155
(Projector and
camera shutter clicks)

101
00:03:56,189 --> 00:03:59,140
As the individual helping
finance this little enterprise,

102
00:03:59,174 --> 00:04:01,643
I'd like to start feeling like
I'm getting my money's worth.

103
00:04:01,677 --> 00:04:03,111
We've still got a month left.

104
00:04:03,145 --> 00:04:04,345
Plenty of time
to turn things around.

105
00:04:04,363 --> 00:04:05,513
That's just whistlin'
past the graveyard.

106
00:04:05,531 --> 00:04:08,033
- We need to do something.
- You have a suggestion?

107
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:10,018
Stack the deck.

108
00:04:10,036 --> 00:04:12,153
I found a computer nerd
of my own,

109
00:04:12,187 --> 00:04:14,656
says he can rig the election
for Grant, easy as pie.

110
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:16,541
- Very funny.
- Am I laughing?

111
00:04:16,575 --> 00:04:18,326
(Lowered voice) Okay.
You saying "rig the election"

112
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:21,880
on a campaign plane is like
joking that you have a bomb

113
00:04:21,914 --> 00:04:23,548
in the security line
at the airport.

114
00:04:23,582 --> 00:04:25,366
You don't do it unless
you want to end up

115
00:04:25,384 --> 00:04:28,169
having your body cavities
searched by big men with guns.

116
00:04:28,203 --> 00:04:30,138
Whoa.
Just trying to help.

117
00:04:30,172 --> 00:04:32,874
We got a problem.
I am a solution man.

118
00:04:32,892 --> 00:04:34,009
Your solution is a felony.

119
00:04:34,043 --> 00:04:35,343
Well, then,
you're the fix-it gal.

120
00:04:35,377 --> 00:04:36,728
Quit bitchin'
and start pitchin'.

121
00:04:36,762 --> 00:04:38,930
(Clears throat)
Those numbers are fatal.

122
00:04:38,981 --> 00:04:40,932
(Clears throat)
What this campaign needs

123
00:04:40,983 --> 00:04:43,601
is a big pointy boot
to kick it square in the ass.

124
00:04:43,652 --> 00:04:45,403
I was thinking... (Sighs)

125
00:04:45,438 --> 00:04:47,906
Maybe it's time
we brought in help.

126
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:50,108
- He's not gonna like it.
- He will learn to like it.

127
00:04:50,110 --> 00:04:50,994
We talking about Jerry?

128
00:04:51,028 --> 00:04:53,028
Fitz's father?
That's... that's brilliant.

129
00:04:53,029 --> 00:04:54,496
I wondered why
he wasn't on the trail.

130
00:04:54,530 --> 00:04:56,331
I figured maybe his health
wasn't good.

131
00:04:56,365 --> 00:04:57,866
(Cyrus) Oh, it's good.

132
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,334
The good senator
Fitzgerald Thomas Grant II's

133
00:04:59,368 --> 00:05:01,169
gonna bury us all.

134
00:05:01,203 --> 00:05:03,755
Fitz has been very clear
about his father.

135
00:05:03,789 --> 00:05:05,390
He'll never agree to it.

136
00:05:05,424 --> 00:05:06,524
That was then.

137
00:05:06,559 --> 00:05:08,242
This is 10 points down.

138
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:09,761
(Projector and camera
shutter clicking)

139
00:05:09,795 --> 00:05:11,930
No! You know better!
You know!

140
00:05:11,964 --> 00:05:13,431
We are losing!
We are lost!

141
00:05:13,466 --> 00:05:14,933
I can win this on my own!

142
00:05:14,967 --> 00:05:17,602
You have political capital!
You need to start spending it!

143
00:05:17,636 --> 00:05:19,721
(Lowered voice) I need to
point out voices carry.

144
00:05:19,755 --> 00:05:21,756
(Sighs) You might want to
either lower the volume

145
00:05:21,774 --> 00:05:24,609
or continue this
conversation in a room.

146
00:05:26,112 --> 00:05:28,229
You talk to him.
He actually listens to you.

147
00:05:28,263 --> 00:05:32,266
(Beep, door opens and slams)

148
00:05:41,009 --> 00:05:42,644
(Panting)

149
00:05:42,678 --> 00:05:44,045
Fitz...
Mm?

150
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,780
We're all concerned that
the campaign needs a spark.

151
00:05:45,798 --> 00:05:47,548
Your father could be it.

152
00:05:47,566 --> 00:05:51,552
And I really don't want to
discuss my father right now.

153
00:05:51,686 --> 00:05:52,270
(Exhales) Mm.

154
00:05:53,004 --> 00:05:54,189
Your father...

155
00:05:55,223 --> 00:05:56,590
Is a national treasure.

156
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:58,559
Self-made man,
two terms as...

157
00:05:58,593 --> 00:06:00,477
Governor, 4-time senator.
I know.

158
00:06:00,528 --> 00:06:02,546
The image of him passing on
the torch to his son...

159
00:06:02,581 --> 00:06:05,032
That will ignite the base.
The press loves him.

160
00:06:05,066 --> 00:06:06,667
Everyone loves him.

161
00:06:06,701 --> 00:06:08,786
<i>I</i> don't want him here.

162
00:06:10,989 --> 00:06:12,372
He can help.

163
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:15,009
You need help right now.

164
00:06:17,796 --> 00:06:20,064
You really think
we're at that place?

165
00:06:20,098 --> 00:06:21,715
We're at that place.

166
00:06:23,417 --> 00:06:24,669
If I say yes,

167
00:06:26,804 --> 00:06:28,271
will you stop talking
about the campaign

168
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:29,655
for the next 20 minutes?

169
00:06:29,689 --> 00:06:31,090
Why?

170
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,860
Hmm...

171
00:06:37,931 --> 00:06:39,149
(Gasps)

172
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,851
The bullet tore
through your frontal lobe.

173
00:06:41,885 --> 00:06:43,853
We managed the swelling,
and with any luck,

174
00:06:43,887 --> 00:06:45,705
the effects you see
will be minimal.

175
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:46,939
Effects such as?

176
00:06:46,973 --> 00:06:48,474
Dizziness, fatigue, irritability.

177
00:06:48,509 --> 00:06:50,493
The symptoms we commonly
associate with concussions.

178
00:06:50,527 --> 00:06:52,211
And if they're not?

179
00:06:52,246 --> 00:06:54,147
Our frontal lobes
control executive function.

180
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:55,965
So sometimes in patients
we've seen

181
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:58,034
an inability to make decisions,
a shorter attention span.

182
00:06:58,068 --> 00:06:59,669
We've had patients who
haven't been able to write,

183
00:06:59,703 --> 00:07:01,304
patients who suffer
from aphasia.

184
00:07:01,338 --> 00:07:02,922
- Aphasia?
- Speech impairment?

185
00:07:02,956 --> 00:07:04,240
Either you can't speak
at all, or if you can,

186
00:07:04,274 --> 00:07:06,292
it's hard to find your words.

187
00:07:06,326 --> 00:07:09,028
We'll also be on the lookout
for changes in personality.

188
00:07:09,063 --> 00:07:10,696
It all depends on the patient.

189
00:07:11,231 --> 00:07:12,715
That's why I want to get
a neurology team in here pronto

190
00:07:12,749 --> 00:07:14,600
- and see where we are.
- So when can I get back to work?

191
00:07:14,634 --> 00:07:16,435
Assuming there's no permanent
damage, three weeks.

192
00:07:16,469 --> 00:07:17,703
(Sighs)

193
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:19,605
Walking across a room
will feel like a marathon.

194
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:21,790
(Knock on door)
Am I interrupting?

195
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:23,225
Thank you, doctor.

196
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:26,412
<i>(Woman speaking</i>
<i>indistinctly over P.A.)</i>

197
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,913
(Door closes)
What is it?

198
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:31,800
I'm afraid we have
a Sally Langston problem.

199
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:34,636
(Projector and camera
shutter clicking)

200
00:07:34,671 --> 00:07:35,837
The letter of reinstatement

201
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:37,272
submitted on behalf
of President Grant

202
00:07:37,306 --> 00:07:40,074
was entirely premature.

203
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:42,927
Regrettably, he is not
in any sort of condition

204
00:07:42,945 --> 00:07:45,080
to resume the powers
and responsibilities

205
00:07:45,114 --> 00:07:48,099
of this office at this time.

206
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:51,736
Understanding, as always,
that our first and only duty

207
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:53,755
is to the American people,

208
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:57,909
I have prepared a document
for your signatures

209
00:07:57,943 --> 00:08:00,328
declaring that we are left no choice

210
00:08:00,362 --> 00:08:03,014
but to challenge President
Grant's fitness...(Door opens)

211
00:08:03,048 --> 00:08:04,365
To again assume...

212
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:08,986
Morning, everyone.

213
00:08:11,123 --> 00:08:12,841
Sorry I'm late.

214
00:08:18,887 --> 00:08:20,355
Are we sure this was
a good idea?

215
00:08:20,406 --> 00:08:21,522
He's just gonna show his face,
shake a few hands,

216
00:08:21,573 --> 00:08:22,874
hear ten minutes
of the briefing,

217
00:08:22,908 --> 00:08:23,941
and go back to bed,

218
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:25,960
and Sally disappears forever

219
00:08:25,995 --> 00:08:28,680
into that political black hole
called the vice presidency.

220
00:08:28,714 --> 00:08:30,431
- He's looking great!
- Guy's a medical miracle.

221
00:08:30,466 --> 00:08:33,868
Madame vice President,
how are you today?

222
00:08:36,355 --> 00:08:38,723
(Laughs)
(Laughs)

223
00:08:38,741 --> 00:08:41,559
That was small of me.
I need to work on that. (Chuckles)

224
00:08:42,993 --> 00:08:44,295
I need a fresh shirt.

225
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:46,847
Ask Izzie to send one down for me.

226
00:08:46,881 --> 00:08:48,182
Why don't you we get you up to bed?

227
00:08:48,216 --> 00:08:49,600
I have to get down
to the sit room.

228
00:08:49,634 --> 00:08:51,168
Fitz, you did it.
You're back.

229
00:08:51,202 --> 00:08:53,036
You're President.
You have nothing to prove.

230
00:08:53,054 --> 00:08:54,955
Until Sally Langston
puts a letter on my desk

231
00:08:54,989 --> 00:08:58,141
accepting my reinstatement,
I have everything to prove.

232
00:08:58,159 --> 00:08:59,843
Have I thanked you for that,
by the way?

233
00:08:59,878 --> 00:09:01,078
For forging my signature

234
00:09:01,112 --> 00:09:02,496
and forcing me
out of the hospital

235
00:09:02,530 --> 00:09:03,697
before my stitches
had healed

236
00:09:03,732 --> 00:09:05,683
to save you from jail
and keep my job?

237
00:09:05,717 --> 00:09:07,935
Thank you.

238
00:09:07,969 --> 00:09:10,621
(Sighs)

239
00:09:11,555 --> 00:09:13,222
I can't show any weakness.

240
00:09:13,257 --> 00:09:14,641
This is not
a show of weakness.

241
00:09:14,675 --> 00:09:17,310
You were shot. You've made
a miraculous recovery.

242
00:09:17,361 --> 00:09:19,112
No one is expecting you
to spend five hours

243
00:09:19,146 --> 00:09:20,496
in a military briefing.

244
00:09:20,531 --> 00:09:23,549
Sally Langston
is dancing around the fire.

245
00:09:23,584 --> 00:09:27,353
She's not gonna stop
until my head's on a stick.

246
00:09:27,404 --> 00:09:29,589
They need to see me,
not her,

247
00:09:29,623 --> 00:09:32,125
being commander-in-chief
of the armed forces.

248
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:34,977
I need a clean shirt.

249
00:09:35,295 --> 00:09:36,846
And that's the difference

